      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 236: The congestion callback runs from the audio RTCP checker thread and directly iterates call RTP session lists and calls into every video session. If getRtpSessionList() is not internally synchronized for concurrent media reconfiguration, this can race with session teardown/reinvite and produce use-after-free or stale session behavior. Prefer scheduling this onto the call/media control thread or using an existing synchronized helper that snapshots sessions under the call lock before invoking callbacks outside that lock.\n```suggestion\n// Pseudocode: dispatch to the call/media executor, then snapshot active video sessions\n// under the call\u0027s synchronization primitive before calling onAudioCongestion().\nthisPtr-\u003erunOnMediaThread([w, audioWeak, audioLoss] {\n    auto call \u003d w.lock();\n    auto audioSession \u003d audioWeak.lock();\n    if (!call || !audioSession || !call-\u003ehasRtpSession(audioSession))\n        return;\n    for (auto\u0026 videoSession : call-\u003egetRtpSessionList(MediaType::MEDIA_VIDEO))\n        if (auto videoRtp \u003d std::dynamic_pointer_cast\u003cvideo::VideoRtpSession\u003e(videoSession))\n            videoRtp-\u003eonAudioCongestion(audioLoss);\n});\n```",
